    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"spell-description\">\n  <p>\n    <strong>School</strong>&nbsp;abjuration;\n    <strong>Level</strong>&nbsp;shaman 5, witch 5;\n    \n    \n    \n    \n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Casting Time</strong>&nbsp;10 minutes<br>\n    <strong>Components</strong>&nbsp;V, S, M (powdered diamond worth 400 gp)<br>\n  </p>\n  <p>\n    <strong>Range</strong>&nbsp;touch<br>\n    <strong>Area</strong>&nbsp;object touched or up to 5 sq. ft./level<br>\n    <strong>Targets</strong>&nbsp;object touched or up to 5 sq. ft./level<br>\n    \n    <strong>Duration</strong>&nbsp;permanent until discharged (D)<br>\n      <strong>Saving Throw</strong>&nbsp;see text;&nbsp;\n      <strong>Spell Resistance</strong>&nbsp;no<br>\n  </p>\n  <h2>Description</h2>\n  <p>This spell functions as @Compendium[pf1.spells.yuftnxwtc9du93ho]{Hex Glyph}, except you can store a hex or a major hex (but not a grand hex). You trace the glyph with incense, which must first be sprinkled with powdered diamond (as noted in the material line).</p>\n<p>@Compendium[pf1.spells.j0bc0iii8zp1jiwr]{Read Magic} allows its caster to identify a greater <em>hex glyph</em> with a DC 16 @Compendium[pf1.skills.uLZI2uWz0uB8UgBc]{Spellcraft} check.</p>\n</div>\n",
